+# ADR-0002 — Three parallel-isolatable pure-utility modules in `src/lib`
+
+- **Status:** Accepted (implemented)
+- **Date:** 2026-05-27
+- **Relates to:** [ADR-0001](./ADR-0001-test-harness-and-pure-logic-coverage.md) (reuses its `node --test` via `tsx` harness)
+
+## Context
+
+`src/lib` already holds small, dependency-free pure helpers (`cn.ts`, `format.ts`).
+The request is to add three more utilities, **deliberately designed to be
+file-disjoint** so they can be implemented in parallel worktrees and merged with
+zero conflicts. The only shared surface is `package.json` test wiring, which is a
+one-time edit owned by ADR-0001 — not a per-module touch point.
+
+Stack: Next.js 16 / React 19 / TypeScript strict, ESM (`"type": "module"`),
+`moduleResolution: bundler`, Node v24.
+
+## Decision
+
+Add three modules, each its own file with its own colocated `*.test.ts`, and
+**no module importing another** (parallel-worktree safe):
+
+1. **`src/lib/slug.ts` — `slugify(text)`**: lowercase → trim → collapse every run
+   of `[^a-z0-9]+` into a single hyphen → strip leading/trailing hyphens.
+   **ASCII-only by design** — accented letters become separators
+   (`Café déjà vu` → `caf-d-j-vu`). Diacritic folding is explicitly out of scope.
+2. **`src/lib/num.ts` — `clamp(value, min, max)` + `roundTo(value, decimals)`**:
+   `clamp` is inclusive, snaps `±Infinity` to a bound, propagates a `NaN` value as
+   `NaN`, and throws `RangeError` on inverted/non-finite bounds. `roundTo` uses an
+   exponential-notation re-parse to beat binary floating-point error
+   (`1.005 → 1.01`); non-finite values pass through unchanged; negative/`NaN`
+   `decimals` coerce to 0.
+3. **`src/lib/str.ts` — `truncate(text, max, ellipsis='…')` + `titleCase(text)`**:
+   `truncate` counts the ellipsis against `max` so the result length never exceeds
+   `max`; `titleCase` uppercases the first char of each word, lowercases the rest,
+   and **preserves original whitespace runs**.
+
+Test files use extensionless relative imports (`./slug`, not `./slug.ts`) to
+satisfy strict `tsc`.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- +25 tests for these three modules (8 slug + 10 num + 7 str), no new framework
+  surface beyond the ADR-0001 harness.
+- The disjoint design is proven: parallel implement/merge is conflict-free outside
+  the single `package.json` test-script edit.
+- ASCII-only `slugify` degrades non-Latin input to separators. If SEO later needs
+  `café → cafe`, that is a separate normalization task, not a change here.
+- Verified this run: `npm test` green, `tsc --noEmit` clean, Node v24.12.0.
+- **Workspace note:** the `src/lib` modules for this ADR were absent at the start of
+  this run and were re-implemented from this settled decision.
+

